## Vault — Storing Secrets Securely

Vault is a Supabase extension that stores secrets encrypted in the database. Use it to store API keys that need to be accessed from Edge Functions or database functions — without putting them in environment variables or code.

### Enable Vault
```
Supabase Dashboard → Database → Extensions → vault → Enable
```

### Store a secret
```sql
-- Store a secret (run once in SQL Editor)
SELECT vault.create_secret(
  'sk-your-openai-api-key',       -- the secret value
  'openai_api_key',                -- your name for it
  'OpenAI API key for embeddings'  -- optional description
);
-- Returns a UUID — save it, use it to read the secret later
```

### Read a secret (from database function or Edge Function)
```sql
-- In a Postgres function
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION get_secret(secret_name TEXT)
RETURNS TEXT LANGUAGE sql SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path = public, vault AS $$
  SELECT decrypted_secret FROM vault.decrypted_secrets WHERE name = secret_name;
$$;

-- Then use in any function
DECLARE
  api_key TEXT := get_secret('openai_api_key');
BEGIN
  -- use api_key
END;
```

```typescript
// In an Edge Function
const { data } = await supabase.rpc('get_secret', { secret_name: 'openai_api_key' })
const apiKey = data  // the actual key value
```

### List stored secrets (names only — values always encrypted)
```sql
SELECT id, name, description, created_at FROM vault.secrets;
```

### Update or delete a secret
```sql
SELECT vault.update_secret('[SECRET_UUID]', 'new-secret-value');
DELETE FROM vault.secrets WHERE name = 'old_secret_name';
```

