## Superuser — What Is and Isn't Allowed on Supabase

Supabase runs managed PostgreSQL. The `postgres` role is not a true superuser.

### Blocked operations (Supabase restrictions)
```sql
-- These will error on Supabase:
COPY table FROM PROGRAM 'command';     -- shell execution blocked
ALTER USER postgres PASSWORD 'new';    -- user management restricted
CREATE USER new_postgres_user;         -- requires superuser
```

### What postgres CAN do on Supabase
```sql
-- All of these work:
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector;   -- install extensions
ALTER TABLE ... ;                         -- schema changes
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION ... ;          -- functions
CREATE TRIGGER ... ;                      -- triggers
GRANT/REVOKE on tables and functions;    -- permissions
ALTER ROLE authenticated SET ... ;        -- role settings
```
